ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2858.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> VS and Trak need Pick Up slots in the rotations.</span><hr size=1> I'm not currently organizing a pick up raid for VS, but if anyone else is then I say more power to them.<br><br>Don't you Uber guilds have bigger fish to fry? Why are you still on Kunark anyway?<br><br>Rotations are good and all until there are sufficient numbers of other who are able to down said mob. Just as Naggy and Vox were so shall VS and Trak be.<br><br>No sense in fighting it, tiss the way of things.<br><br>If there is consistant argument against pickups it will only serve to strengthen the resolve of people like me- forcing us to create more pick up raids to prove that it CAN be done.<br><br>These mobs don't belong to anyone, rotations are a courtesy only...<br><br>If ya want to be really smart about things and keep the rotation in tact then it would be wise to assign a slot or two for pick ups. As it is now these slots will not likely be filled up- but to avoid the chaos (that everyone fears so much) why not assign a pickup slot for VS and Trak?<br><br>Keep in mind that the rotation was set up so that uber guilds didnt step on each others toes. For ALL the rest of the people not in a guild currently on rotation it is a fun prospect to have a chance to even see the uber mobs (VS TRAK VOX NAGGY ETC.) let alone have a chance at nice gear or an epic crucial piece.  It's nice that you uber guilds are friendly to one another in allowing &quot;turns&quot; at said mobs- but where do all the little people fit in?<br><br>This game SHOULD NOT be a members only or elitist club. Infact it SHOULD be quite the opposite, all inclusive and non discriminative allowing all people to fight and have fun doing whatever they like.  These uber mobs are not yours to police and yet ... a balance must be found.<br><br>FFA may scare many of you- really if you are an Uber guild then the FFA only scares you if you are going up against other uber guilds. SO I say avoid FFA by puting pickup raids on your rotation schedule.<br><br>Bluntly let me say that if I am not on your rotation list then I am not bound by your rotation schedule. If you want to avoid this scarry (/shiver) type of chaos then add multiple slots for pickup raids. Though they will not likely be successful at first, eventually they will- and hoo raay for those that acomplish it.<br><br>If you don't like the idea of VS or Trak being on pickups and rotations then all I have to say to you is watch out you're about to get run over by the reality train.<br><br>Sure there should be stipulations, we can't have guilds attacking the same shit all the time, look at the mess up on hate when affliction and MF were up there- so point well taken- lets establish a few slots for pick ups- even if the pickups don't succeed it would be wise to attempt to include everyone on these mobs.<br><br>If ya don't ya risk an all out FFA- and that really is what everyone seems to want to avoid.<br><br>-Dunkamar<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uiceweaselx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ice Weasel X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 298<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/3/02 2:29:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2858.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VS and Trak need Pick Up slots in the rotations.</span><hr size=1> Hmm, in the other post in the D&P board I was under the impression that you were in favor of multiple pickups per rotation. &nbsp;I guess you didn't realize that VS already has pickups in the rotation. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=t